
---

### 🐙 3. **Upload to GitHub**

#### Option A: GitHub Web Upload (Easy)

1. Go to [github.com](https://github.com) and sign in.
2. Click `New` repository → Name: `fire-alarm-system`
3. Create it.
4. On the new repo page, click “Upload files” → drag your folder contents in.
5. Click “Commit changes”.

#### Option B: Using Git CLI (Professional Way)

```bash
# Navigate to your project folder
cd fire-alarm-system

# Initialize Git
git init

# Add files
git add .

# Commit
git commit -m "Initial commit: Fire Alarm Detection System"

# Create repo on GitHub and copy its HTTPS URL (e.g., https://github.com/yourname/fire-alarm-system.git)

# Add remote and push
git remote add origin https://github.com/yourname/fire-alarm-system.git
git push -u origin master
